00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:18,000
 Jacob is holistic in his wrestling.

262
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,040
 He doesn't just leave it to his brother.

263
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:22,280
 He continues wrestling in other aspects of his life.

264
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,760
 His brother wants to kill him

265
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:26,200
 because he has taken what belonged to him.

266
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,680
 So Jacob runs and flees

267
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:30,720
 and he meets this woman named Rachel.

268
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,720
 Beautiful woman, I guess,

269
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:34,400
 because he's willing to enter into a contract

270
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:38,600
 to work seven years so that he can marry her.

271
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,240
 The story goes he works seven years

272
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,600
 and he thinks he's gonna get Rachel.

273
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:48,240
 On the wedding day, he actually doesn't get Rachel.

274
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,600
 The dad tricked him.

275
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,880
 The dad deceived him.

276
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,240
 The dad wrestled with him.

277
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:56,520
 And actually he gives him the other daughter, Leah.

278
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:59,720
 And Jacob's annoyed because, Bible says this,

279
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:03,040
 Rachel was the beautiful one, Leah was not so much.

280
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:07,480
 So he couldn't get Rachel because he had just gotten Leah.

281
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,480
 So the father's like, well, if you want Rachel,

282
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,600
 I'm not gonna give you both of my daughters for one price.

283
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,600
 You have to work another seven more years.

284
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,360
 So Jacob's been working for 14 years

285
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,640
 just to get the thing he thought he deserved.

286
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:21,520
 Wrestling.

287
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:22,360
 And it continues.

288
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:27,360
 His land and his property, his sheep and his cattle end up,

289
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,720
 him and Laban live in the same area.

290
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:30,960
 They've decided to separate into two parts of the space

291
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,800
 so that there would be no mixing.

292
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,520
 And all of Laban's things would be Laban's,

293
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,200
 all of Jacob's things would be Jacob's.

294
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:40,040
 But all of Jacob's cattle are bigger and stronger

295
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:42,760
 and look better and look healthier than Laban's,

296
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:46,360
 which creates conflict between him and his father-in-law.

297
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,200
 Wrestling.

298
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,200
 This theme of wrestling just continues

299
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,080
 and continues for Jacob.

300
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:54,240
 He wrestles with Esau.

301
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:57,160
 He wrestles with Laban.

302
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,040
 He uses strategy to try and figure out

303
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,640
 how do I get myself out of these situations?

304
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:03,320
 How do I get what I deserve?

305
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:05,240
 He fights, he wrestles.

306
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,320
 This is just his life at this point.

307
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:12,520
 But it would appear that God wanted more

308
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,720
 from him and of him.

309
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,400
 And so when we take a look here at Genesis 32

310
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:20,880
 where we have that famous encounter,

311
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,320
 starting at verse 22, it says this.

312
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:25,400
 The same night he, speaking of Jacob, arose,

313
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,520
 took his two wives, his two female servants,

314
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:33,040
 his 11 children, crossed the ford at Jabbok.

315
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,440
 He took them and sent them across the stream

316
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,400
 and everything else that he had.

317
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,400
 And Jacob was left alone.

318
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:44,080
 And a man wrestled with him until the breaking of the day.

319
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,480
 When the man saw that he did not prevail against Jacob,

320
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,880
 he touched his hip socket and Jacob's hip

321
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,880
 was put out of joint as he wrestled with him.

322
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,240
 Then he said, "Let me go for the day is broken."

323
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,280
 But Jacob said, "I will not let you go

324
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:59,040
 unless you bless me."

325
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,240
 And he said, "What is your name?"

326
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,280
 He said, "Jacob."

327
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,880
 Then he said, "You shall no longer be called Jacob,

328
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:07,720
 but Israel, for you have striven with God and with men

329
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,880
 and have prevailed."

330
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:13,280
 Then Jacob asked him, "Please tell me your name."

331
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:15,840
 But he said, "Why is it that you ask my name?"

332
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,080
 And there he blessed him.

333
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:21,800
 So Jacob called the name of this place Peniel,

334
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,240
 saying, "I have seen God face to face

335
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:27,240
 and yet my life has been delivered."

336
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:29,040
 What has happened in this moment?

337
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:31,120
 Just a little bit of more context

338
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,160
 so that we really get this wrestle

339
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:35,960
 because this is a massive encounter with God.

340
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:38,160
 This is an orthodox encounter with God.

341
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,320
 We have to understand.

342
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,120
 So Jacob is getting ready to go back home.

343
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,920
 He's been away from home for all these years

344
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:47,000
 and he's carrying his family and all the things he has.

345
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,600
 And he gets word that his brother,

346
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,760
 who hated him, wanted to kill him, was ahead of him.

347
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:54,520
 So naturally that scares him.

348
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:55,520
 Then the word gets worse.

349
00:13:55,520 --> 00:14:00,520
 His brother is with 400 men ahead of him.

350
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:03,000
 Naturally, Jacob gets a little nervous,

351
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,320
 slows down a little bit and thinks,

352
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,240
 "Okay, well, what do I do?

353
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,440
 I have a wife, I have two wives, I have kids,

354
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,280
 I have 11 children, I have all this stuff.

355
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,600
 How are we gonna make it if my brother

356
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,440
 wants revenge for what I've done?"

357
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:16,480
 He is in a desperate, broken moment.

358
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,680
 So he gets clever.

359
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:21,400
 He sends some of his best stuff ahead.

360
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,960
 He goes, "Take this to Esau."

361
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:26,600
 And you see Esau say, "These are gifts from Jacob."

362
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,360
 So he tries to use a little bit of cleverness, strategy,

363
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:32,280
 maybe not trickery, but a little bit of deceit.

364
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,440
 He doesn't really wanna give him gifts.

365
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,360
 He just doesn't wanna get killed, right?

366
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,200
 Makes sense.

367
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,160
 He's doing the best that he can.

368
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,240
 He's doing what he thinks he needs to do,

369
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:40,080
 but he's worried.

370
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,480
 He's at his lowest point here.

371
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:46,160
 He has all this stuff, yet he still is at this moment of,

372
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,200
 "What do I do?"

373
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:52,200
 And tension and brokenness, the unexpected, then happens.

374
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,600
 He's unprepared, and unexpectedly,

375
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,760
 he has this encounter with God in the form of a fight.

376
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,840
 I'm just gonna be honest.

377
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:03,280
 When I encounter God, I hope he's not trying to fight me.

378
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:05,680
 Right, like that must have been a moment.

379
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:08,220
 But how poetically beautiful is it

380
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:11,320
 that most of Jacob's life has been marked symbolically

381
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,960
 with this aspect of wrestling.

382
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,960
 And when he encounters God,

383
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:19,240
 his encounter with him is through what?

384
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,400
 Through a wrestle, through a struggle.

385
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:26,400
 God meets him in a language that he is overly familiar with.

386
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,600
 And the first thing we have to note here

387
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:32,080
 is how God meets him on these challenging terms.

388
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:35,040
 The context of his situation were not ideal.

389
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:39,840
 God meets him here in his mess, in his brokenness.

390
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:43,560
 When we need him the most, that's when God meets us.

391
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,660
 And I think it's something that we have to keep in mind

392
00:15:45,660 --> 00:15:48,600
 because a lot of us subconsciously live in a way

393
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,600
 that seeks out pleasure and avoids pain.

394
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,560
 But what if it's in the pain

395
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,400
 that God plans to speak the loudest?

396
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:59,320
 What if it's in the pain that God plans on encountering you?

397
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:04,420
 If our life is constantly avoiding the difficult,

398
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:10,380
 do we potentially avoid these encounters with God?

399
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:11,880
 So if you're struggling,

400
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:14,860
 if you're in a place of brokenness,

401
00:16:14,860 --> 00:16:17,600
 if your life is going less than expected,

402
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,240
 if you've run into unexpected conflict and trouble

403
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,040
 and things just don't seem right,

404
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:24,660
 if you're in your darkest place,

405
00:16:24,660 --> 00:16:27,000
 if you're in a moment of tension and pain,

406
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:29,600
 if your circumstances leave you desperate,

407
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:32,420
 that's an open door for an encounter.

408
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:35,680
 That's what we see here in Jacob.

409
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:39,860
 God has a funny way of showing up most clear

410
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:41,840
 in our darkest hours.

411
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,160
 And so I wonder what would happen

412
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,480
 if in those moments of darkness,

413
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:48,380
 we sought him instead of running away?

414
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:54,280
 It leads me to the second thing that I notice in this story,

415
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,840
 and that's around prayer,

416
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:59,560
 how prayer is essential to an encounter with God.

417
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,080
 So that's exactly what Jacob does.

418
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,760
 In verse nine, he prays.

