00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:26,460
 "Please deliver me from the hand of my brother,

430
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:28,240
 "from the hand of Esau," listen to this,

431
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,120
 "for I fear him."

432
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:34,800
 I love that Jacob, when he prays in this moment,

433
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:38,280
 before he does anything, he doesn't have the best words.

434
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:41,440
 This isn't like super sophisticated big man prayer, right?

435
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:44,240
 He's not using anything fancy.

436
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:47,520
 He's just positioning himself authentically

437
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,840
 in front of God.

438
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,560
 He doesn't have to have a seminary degree.

439
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,360
 He doesn't have to have been in church for all his life.

440
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:55,280
 He's just exposing his heart to God.

441
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,960
 We can do this, right?

