00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,840
 I don't know how it's happened.

465
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:57,440
 I don't even think I deserve it.

466
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:00,560
 I've been unworthy of this, but you have been good.

467
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:05,120
 He recalls the faithfulness of God.

468
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:08,160
 His desperation does not blind him

469
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:10,480
 from the reality that God has been there

470
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,980
 and God has been blessing him.

471
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:15,240
 And then his prayer changes a bit.

472
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:18,040
 He pours out his heart to God.

473
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:20,280
 My favorite thing that I learned in this entire passage

474
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,840
 when I was studying it was just,

475
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:22,680
 there's nothing I didn't learn,

476
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,360
 I just read it and it hit me hard.

477
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:28,360
 He says, "I fear him, I fear Esau."

478
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,920
 That is as clear, that is as honest,

479
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,980
 probably as vulnerable as it gets.

480
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:36,920
 He's raw, he's not trying to come up

481
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,760
 with anything strategic, he's not trying

482
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,920
 to over-spiritualize or say it's this or say it's that

483
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,400
 or use some big fancy words.

484
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:47,080
 He is just being bare in front of God.

485
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,440
 That level of authenticity,

486
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:52,880
 that level of purely exposing where your heart is,

487
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:55,760
 no pretentiousness, no big words,

488
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,400
 just showing God your heart.

489
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:01,080
 What if that's an element to prayer?

