00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,840
 We just all of a sudden are floating on clouds

523
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:27,000
 and we're more holy.

524
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,000
 We no longer deal with temptation anymore.

525
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,640
 That's actually not how it works.

526
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:33,480
 We've got to have the right picture of prayer.

527
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:34,800
 Sometimes you're gonna pray

528
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,400
 and you're still gonna struggle.

529
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:39,120
 That's the reality of our life.

530
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:40,880
 I'm so glad that's clear in here.

531
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:43,720
 He leans back on his human tendency

532
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,040
 to control his next steps.

533
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:50,000
 But he's opened up a door.

534
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,840
 By praying, he's started something.

535
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:57,440
 He's allowed something to happen.

536
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,040
 And then it does, it happens.

537
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,440
 He prayed in the beginning of the night.

538
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:03,880
 Later in the night, he has his encounter with God.

539
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,760
 And his encounter comes with a wrestle,

540
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,880
 which I think is weird.

541
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,880
 Like of all the crazy things God can do

542
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,680
 when he encounters you, like I guess for me,

543
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:13,520
 sign me up, I don't wanna wrestle God.

544
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:16,080
 I would much rather just have him talk to me

545
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:17,440
 and tell me who I am, all these things.

546
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,280
 But Jacob ends up wrestling him.

547
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:21,240
 And I'm pretty convinced Jacob had no idea

548
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,440
 it was God at first.

549
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:23,560
 It's the dark of night.

550
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:26,680
 He probably thinks maybe Esau sent somebody

551
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:29,280
 knowing I was coming to take me out.

552
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:31,000
 Maybe there's thieves and robbers around

553
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,120
 trying to take my stuff.

554
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,480
 I mean, I'm carrying all this stuff.

555
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,760
 I'm a well-off guy.

556
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,320
 He wrestles this guy, probably in self-defense.

557
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,880
 But at some point, something clicks in his head.

558
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:40,920
 This isn't human.

559
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:44,080
 I'm wrestling divinity.

560
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:48,440
 I am pushing against the creator of the universe.

561
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:51,160
 He becomes aware that he's wrestling with God.

562
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,160
 And what does he do?

563
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:54,200
 He doesn't let go.

564
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:57,440
 He holds on.

565
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,560
 He digs his heels in.

566
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:03,440
 He wholly commits himself to the fight.

567
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,320
 He holds on more.

568
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:07,160
 He struggles, he fights.

569
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,400
 He even gets his hip displaced.

570
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:12,440
 Fun fact, don't fight God, he'll break your hip.

571
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,680
 That's my takeaway today.

572
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:19,360
 But even in that space, it seems like that's when

573
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:22,160
 the change actually starts to begin.

574
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:26,880
 See, the old Jacob, his strategy, his way,

575
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:31,040
 his preference in doing things was through deception.

576
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:32,240
 The old Jacob would have tried to,

577
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,640
 when he realized this was God,

578
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,520
 he would have tried to deceive him.

579
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:37,080
 He would have tried to supplant.

580
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:39,360
 He would have tried to trick or try to get ahead

581
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,640
 or get something out of him.

582
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:42,920
 He would have tried to get his own way.

583
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:46,600
 But instead, he wrestles him,

584
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,560
 which means he just holds on to him.

585
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,880
 Like, it doesn't say that he beats up God, right?

586
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,800
 Or God beats him up.

587
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:52,760
 He fights with him.

588
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:57,440
 He's against, he's holding on with all that he has.

589
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:58,880
 It feels like it's in that moment, he's like,

590
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:01,600
 "God, if this is you, I have you.

591
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,520
 "I have your attention, you have mine,

592
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:05,560
 "and I'm not gonna let you go."

593
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:08,000
 That is his wrestle.

594
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,800
 It's a clinging on to God.

595
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:15,200
 With his one chance, he stays, he wrestles.

596
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:20,200
 He's got everything to lose, but Jacob clings to God.

597
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:25,160
 A clear indicator of his transformation

598
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:30,160
 in the middle of all of this is that Jacob then asks,

599
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,760
 what do I mean by this?

600
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:35,040
 Well, so far, Jacob has been really good at taking, right?

601
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,600
 He's been really good at being clever,

602
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,480
 and whatever he thought was his,

603
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:41,080
 he would reach for it, he would take it.

604
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:43,880
 Think specifically to the birthright situation.

605
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:46,760
 There was a whole prophecy around how he would be the one

606
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:48,880
 who would get the inheritance.

607
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:50,960
 But when things didn't go the way he thought,

608
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:52,240
 when it looked challenging,

609
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:54,160
 when it seemed like it was out of reach

610
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:55,560
 and God wasn't gonna do anything,

611
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:58,480
 he took it upon himself to get

612
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,080
 what he thought belonged to him.

613
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,520
 So that would be the natural way

614
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:05,760
 that Jacob would engage in this space, but he asks.

615
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:08,240
 He asks.

616
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:10,520
 I think this is a big thing for a lot of us,

617
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:12,400
 because a lot of us live lives

618
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:16,240
 where we've got to take to get what we need.

619
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:17,440
 No one's really looking out for us.

620
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:19,920
 If I don't look out for me, who's gonna look out for me?

621
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:22,880
 And so we strive and we push and we take

622
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,680
 and we reach and we grab.

623
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,600
 If there's an obstacle in front of me and what I need,

624
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:28,120
 I've got to figure out a way to get it.

625
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:31,080
 We reach for whatever is around us.

626
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:34,280
 This is the natural way that our city operates.

627
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:37,560
 And this is the reality.

628
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:40,880
 Getting the right things the wrong way

629
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,640
 will never actually satisfy you.

630
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,840
 I mean, think about it.

631
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,160
 Jacob already got the blessing.

632
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:48,000
 Isaac actually blessed him.

633
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,640
 Esau actually gave away his birthright.

634
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,040
 He's already received the blessing.

635
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,440
 What is he fighting for?

636
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:55,720
 He's received the blessing, but he's in a moment

637
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,520
 where he's terrified to go forward,

638
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:58,760
 where his whole world could be lost.

639
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,040
 He's received the blessing,

640
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:02,680
 but he's petrified to move forward.

641
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:03,920
 He has a wife and kids.

642
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:05,520
 He has all the material things.

643
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:09,400
 He's been blessed, but yet he's in the darkest,

644
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:12,040
 most tense moment of his life.

645
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:15,760
 He's taken rather than received.

646
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:17,560
 And this is actually something that we can trace back

647
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:19,960
 to the beginning of scripture in Genesis.

648
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:22,080
 We know that Adam and Eve, that the tree,

649
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,280
 the fruit on the tree looked desirable,

650
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:25,280
 looked good for eating.

651
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,440
 And when they are deceived, what do they do?

652
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:31,760
 Rather than going to the maker and asking him for it,

653
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:35,920
 they reach, they take for themselves.

654
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:39,360
 They become their own gods.

655
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:42,720
 And in doing that, they end up wrecking a relationship,

656
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:45,480
 absolutely breaking the relationship with them

657
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:46,360
 and God.

658
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:49,360
 So here's a crazy thought then.

659
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:53,800
 Maybe the real blessing isn't the things we receive,

660
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:57,560
 but maybe it's the relationship we open up

661
00:26:57,560 --> 00:27:00,440
 with the one who gives the thing in the first place.

662
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:05,280
 What if that's the whole thing?

663
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:07,720
 What if the true blessing is that relationship

664
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,680
 with the one who created it all,

665
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:13,000
 with the giver of the gift, not just the gift?

666
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,920
 And I think what happens is when we reach,

667
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:19,960
 we bypass the giver and we get the stuff,

668
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:23,920
 or at least the best that we can reach for.

669
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:26,200
 And I wonder how many times in our life

670
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:29,640
 God is planning to intervene, to meet us where we are,

671
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,600
 to show up, to give us what we need,

672
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:36,000
 but we end up taking matters into our own hands.

673
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:39,080
 We end up filling our hands with the things

674
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:42,720
 that we can reach for, giving us absolutely no space

675
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:45,480
 to receive the thing he has for us.

676
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:49,120
 We end up filling ourselves with these

677
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:53,120
 lesser store brand blessings that really don't fulfill us

678
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:54,040
 in the first place.

679
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:56,520
 We end up becoming our own heroes, our own God.

680
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:59,200
 We settle for the beta version, not the true thing.

681
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:02,680
 And Jacob in this moment has had enough of what he can do.

682
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:07,000
 He's seen what his striving and what his reaching

683
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,080
 has done for him.

684
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:11,680
 And it's not enough.

685
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:15,200
 So he reaches this point and in this encounter,

686
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:17,880
 he asks for the blessing.

687
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,080
 Slight difference.

688
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:23,000
 He asks for the blessing versus taking the blessing.

689
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,040
 And that changes everything.

690
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:28,080
 I wonder what it would take for us

691
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,600
 to reach that point as well,

692
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:34,880
 where we recognize that actually,

693
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,080
 he says, "Knock, the door will be opened.

694
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,760
 "Ask and you will receive."

695
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:41,480
 The father withholds no good gift from his children.

696
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:44,440
 He actually says in scripture that if you wicked people

697
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:47,480
 can give your kids food and good gifts,

698
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:51,280
 how much more am I gonna give you things?

699
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:53,360
 Later in the New Testament, it says that every good

700
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:55,960
 and perfect thing comes from the father above.

701
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:58,760
 He is good and a giver of good stuff,

702
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:00,560
 but we're not gonna be able to see that.

703
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:02,240
 We're not gonna be able to receive that

704
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:06,000
 if we've taken for ourselves the best of what we can grab,

705
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,440
 the best of what we can do.

706
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,960
 This was Jacob.

707
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:14,720
 This was his dark moment, his lonely moment.

708
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:17,440
 His encounter was so unorthodox,

709
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:20,640
 yet his healing was in his wrestle.

710
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:24,280
 And like he should, like we should,

711
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:29,280
 he wrestles through the night till dawn and he prevails.

712
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:30,640
 And what does it mean for him to prevail?

713
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:32,760
 It means that the old him has gone

714
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,720
 and a new version of him has come.

715
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:37,360
 He is no longer Jacob the deceiver.

716
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:40,200
 He is now Jacob the requester.

717
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:41,440
 He's truly prevailed.

718
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:44,460
 He has asked and God has blessed him.

719
00:29:44,460 --> 00:29:48,260
 This encounter has been successful.

720
00:29:48,260 --> 00:29:51,080
 God has met with him and he gets blessed,

721
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,680
 but I think there's a couple of details

722
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:55,840
 we need to really sit on before we continue.

723
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:57,400
 His situation hasn't changed.

724
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:59,160
 Has anyone noticed that yet?

725
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:01,760
 He meets with God as this awesome encounter,

726
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:04,140
 wrestles God, sees him face to face,

727
00:30:04,140 --> 00:30:06,120
 but he still has a brother that might wanna kill him

728
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,840
 with 400 men.

729
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:09,320
 And his encounter with God didn't come

730
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:14,120
 with 400 mercenary angels ready to fight on his behalf.

731
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:17,740
 It didn't come with extra strength to be able to fight.

732
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:19,820
 Actually, let's see, what does this encounter

733
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:20,660
 actually produce?

734
00:30:20,660 --> 00:30:23,120
 It says, "Your name shall no longer be called Jacob,

735
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:25,060
 "but Israel, for you have striven with God

736
00:30:25,060 --> 00:30:26,600
 "and with men and you've prevailed."

737
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:30,800
 So in his asking of God, in his big encounter moment,

738
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:32,080
 he's finally done it all right.

739
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,200
 And what does he get?

740
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:35,480
 A limp and a new name.

741
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,520
 Take that to the battle.

742
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:38,720
 How does that even work?

743
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,600
 Think about this.

744
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,040
 It wasn't until Jethro pointed it out

745
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,520
 in our conversation about it.

746
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:44,440
 So this is his point, not mine.

747
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:47,480
 Jacob is now more vulnerable because he met with God.

748
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:49,280
 He actually can't defend himself.

749
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:52,440
 See, sometimes we think if we just pray,

750
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:54,240
 we're gonna have all the strength to do everything

751
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:56,600
 and we're just gonna have these results happen overnight.

752
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,240
 What happens when you pray

753
00:30:58,240 --> 00:31:00,520
 and somehow you're more vulnerable afterwards?

754
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:01,900
 Have you ever felt that way?

755
00:31:01,900 --> 00:31:04,320
 Where you poured out your heart to God

756
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:07,240
 and your situation hasn't changed immediately?

757
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:09,600
 Maybe you've walked away with a spiritual limp.

758
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:13,780
 God gives him a limp and a new name.

759
00:31:13,780 --> 00:31:16,080
 But here's the thing.

760
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:17,900
 The blessing from his encounter with God

761
00:31:17,900 --> 00:31:20,000
 is gonna be for who Jacob is at the core.

762
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:24,520
 God blesses him by changing not just his name,

763
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:25,440
 but now his identity.

764
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,760
 If you remember what I said earlier in this sermon,

765
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,720
 the name is so important.

766
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:31,560
 The name speaks to who you are.

767
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:32,800
 It speaks to what you're gonna do.

768
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:34,280
 It speaks to what you have done.

769
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:36,520
 It is, in essence, your identity.

770
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:39,160
 The whole of you can be wrapped up in your name.

771
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:42,040
 And so now after experiencing and encountering God

772
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,360
 in this way, he's no longer Jacob the trickster,

773
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,680
 no longer Jacob the supplant or the heel grabber,

774
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,720
 the one who tries to cheat to get ahead.

775
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:52,560
 He is now Israel, the one who fought and wrestled with God

776
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:54,400
 and has been changed and prevailed.

777
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:59,200
 God, in essence, has changed the entirety of who Jacob is.

778
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:04,000
 God renames him something from their encounter,

779
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,960
 but something for his future.

780
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:09,680
 Jacob is able to enter this same challenging

781
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:13,040
 and hard and tense and broken situation,

782
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:15,240
 all the same that it was,

783
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:16,760
 but as a completely different person

784
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:18,340
 with a completely new identity,

785
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:20,880
